---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="YAML Schema">
  <p>Every DDF file has a root key that declares the document type. Currently supported: <code>presentation</code>.</p>

  <h2>Top-level Structure</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">presentation:
  layout: "16x9"          # or "4x3"
  title: "Deck Title"     # metadata
  author: "Author Name"   # metadata

  theme: ...              # colors, fonts
  masters: ...            # reusable slide templates
  slides: ...             # slide content</code></pre>

  <h2>Root Keys</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>layout</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Slide aspect ratio: <code>"16x9"</code> (default) or <code>"4x3"</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>title</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Presentation title (metadata)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>author</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Author name (metadata)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>theme</code></td><td>object</td><td>No</td><td>Theme definition (see <a href="/docs/themes/">Themes</a>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>masters</code></td><td>object</td><td>No</td><td>Named slide templates (see <a href="/docs/masters/">Masters</a>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>slides</code></td><td>array</td><td>Yes</td><td>List of slides (see <a href="/docs/slides/">Slides</a>)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Units</h2>
  <p>All position and size values (<code>x</code>, <code>y</code>, <code>w</code>, <code>h</code>) are in <strong>inches</strong>. A 16:9 slide is 10" x 5.625".</p>

  <h2>Future Root Keys</h2>
  <p>Planned but not yet implemented:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>document:</code> — for .docx output</li>
    <li><code>pdf:</code> — for .pdf output</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  th {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
